Landing Zone:

1. Enable control tower
2. Create an OU structure based on the design
3. Apply SCP on those OU based on the design
4. Enable IAM Identity center and then delegate security-tooling account as the admin
5. Enable Guard Duty and delegate admin to security-tooling
6. Configure Guardduty logs to be pushed to Log-archive account
7. Configure Security lake service for centralised log management of Cloudtrail and VPCFlow logs -  SIEM Integraiton with QRadar
8. Configure Azure AD to IAM Identity center Integration.
9. Deploy VPC for network account (Inspection VPC and Egress VPC)
10.Deploy TGW and attach the VPC together
11.Deploy AWS network firewall in Network account Inspection VPC and delegate the administration to firewall manager deployed in security-tooling account
12.Configure the network routing across for Egress traffic with inspection and ingress traffic with inspection
13.Privilege escalation deploy TEAMS (https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/security/temporary-elevated-access-management-with-iam-identity-center/)
14.Create the config rules for some basic compliance (EBS encryption, Root access check)
15.Configure security hub and delegate security-tooling account as admin for centralising the security logs
16.Configure Client2Site VPN connection (openvpn cloud connexa)
17.Configure a Site2Site VPN connection.
18.Configure a Direct Connect connection.
19. 

Infrastructure:

1. Deploy Dev environment of GATI using IAC
2. create CICD using Terraform cloud

Devsecops:

1. Deploy Jenkins on tooling account
2. Configure jenkins for devsecops tools like Git, JMeter, Selenium, SonarQube, Clair, selenium, JMeter, Nexus, Device Farm GIT, Container registry and AWS code commit for code commit

Application:

1. Configure jenkins for Application Build and Deployment
2. CICD process in place for build and deployment